Quickstrike:





Quickstrike slowly opened his eyes. He groaned, feeling like something was 
pushing him down. He had better days. He thought for a few seconds that he 
was under something. He may have been hit by something hard, because he felt 
groggy.

He looked at the ground by his arm. There was a familiar scent to the air. A 
foul smell.

He rapidly blinked his eyes, trying to focus his optic sensors. There were 
harsh lights mounted around certain parts of the area. The rocky ground 
below his metal body was a blue in color. There were pulsating sound 
near-by.
